[normal],
[normal] and more evidence to tell me what is going to happen and why.  
[normal]Q9 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Chair[bold]:[bold] What marks would you give the Shakespeare 
[normal]r
[normal]eview?  
[normal]Professor Margetts:[bold] I think the same.  It was good, but both these things 
[normal]are lacking feedback loops that would somehow make these things happen.  It is no good just putting data out there and somehow thinking it will float off into the stratosphere, make things better and achieve these three aims.  You need some mechanism for evaluating whether that is happening.  That is what is so difficult.  We are trying to do some of that at the Oxford Internet Institute.  We are doing a systematic analysis of the data.gov platform, but some of the 
[normal]information you need just is not there.  
[normal]Dr Worthy:[bold] There are some very interesting id
[normal]eas in the Shakespear
[normal]e 
[normal]r
[normal]eview. 
[normal] 
[normal]There is 
[normal]the need for a more coherent strategy
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]with its emphasis on citizens as users
[normal],
[normal] and the need for a feedback loop is very important.  I have mainly been working with local government
[normal],
[normal] and one of the
[normal]ir
[normal] points 
[normal]is they 
[normal]want 
[normal]to see what is in it for them
[normal] in terms of public authorities.  A lot of the talk is about what will happen for citizens, businesses and others.  
[normal]A 
[normal]selling point being missed
[normal] 
[normal]is how this 
[normal]sort of 
[normal]data could 
[normal]really transform 
[normal]how policies are made and 
[normal]resources are 
[normal]allocated.  
[normal]If you could develop applications that traced down to the street level how money is spent
[normal],
[normal] that could make a huge difference to how a local authority makes policy
[normal] and 
[normal]decisions
[normal],
[normal] and how it allocates resources.  Homelessness is one area that springs to mind.  
[normal]The 
[normal]Government 
[normal]probably 
[normal]need
[normal] to sell more strongly what is in it for a public authority
[normal],
[normal] as well as helping the public and other groups.
[normal]  
