[normal]Q20 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Mr Reed:[bold] 
[normal]How have open data initiatives transformed or changed public services?
[normal]Professor Margetts:[bold] 
[normal]They have not
[normal],
[normal] for some of the reasons we have been talking about
[normal],
[normal] because of the lack
[normal] of
[normal] 
[normal]feedback loops.  
[normal]If one or more of these 14,000 data sets contained some really important information about the difference between contract providers, service providers or policing services, i
[normal]t is not very clear what the feedback loops are for that information to get back to the Department that has produced the data.  
[normal]It is very much what Beth
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Noveck called “
[normal]throwing 
[normal]data over the transom”.  You throw it over
[normal],
[normal] and then it floats off and it is good.  
[normal]Without the feedback loops
[normal],
[normal] it would be very difficult to point to that.  
