[normal]Dr Pollock:[bold] 
[normal]Our first point is that the Government here in the 
[normal]UK
[normal] 
[normal]have 
[normal]been a leader globally in this agenda.  This Government and even the previous Government took serious steps to open up information and
[normal],
[normal] to some extent
[normal],
[normal] set policy.  There are some obvious lacunae in that, but on the whole I think the Government 
[normal]have 
[normal]been leading.  There is a question at the present time
[normal]—
[normal]we do not want the Government to rest on 
[normal]their 
[normal]laurels.  While there have been some very good achievements, there is still much to be done.  
[normal]Most fundamentally
[normal],
[normal] one of the big
[normal] lacks
[normal]—
[normal]Tom was on
