[normal] there is no embedding of this agenda in legislation beyond what exists 
[normal]in FOI or things like that.  
[normal]One of the greatest challenges is the certainty and the fact that, for example, you do not have this embedded in procurement rules.  You do not have
[normal] it whenever the Government buy
[normal] a new IT system or every time 
[normal]they decide
[normal] to outsource a service.  It should still be the case that relevant data is still controlled by the Government.  One of the biggest risks and dangers we have seen evidence of both in the 
[normal]US
[normal] and here is 
[normal]that 
[normal]you outsource some service 
[normal]and
