[normal]Heather Savory[bold]: 
[normal]I just wanted to come in and say I support what Rufus is saying.  There is a 
[normal]particular issue with some of the
[normal] trading funds.  That is because they are last century’s model.  They have essentially a funding model.  They are set up as bodies that are required to self-fund through commercial activity.  
[normal]I was introduced to the four main trading funds
[normal] here: Companies House, the Land Registry, Ordnance Survey and the Met Office.  
[normal]I refer to 
[normal]them 
[normal]as four non-identical twins.  
[normal]They are not all the same; they all do very different specialised work.  When you get under the skin of this, what you see is that the Land Registry has a very 
[normal]good
