[normal]price-
[normal]paid data for housing and we have recently been able to persuade them to release something called the 
[normal]INSPIRE database, which 
[normal]is
[normal] boundaries for properties.  The 
[normal]Met Office has a good open data programme and Ordnance Survey also 
[normal]has a very successful open data programme, but it does not go far enough if you think about it in the wider economic terms 
[normal]in which 
[normal]we should now be thinking about it.  
[normal]They have a funding model; the Treasury gets a small amount of return.  The 
[normal]Government 
[normal]have 
[normal]to pay for weather services
[normal] and 
[normal]for geographic services.  These are esse
[normal]ntial components 
[normal]of our society, and
[normal] 
